content.description: This rock is underwater when the reservoir is full!!!! If water is low, this boulder is pretty fun for a slippery crack. All of the holds kind of suck, and the top out is a little goofy. When this was FA it was over a 100 degrees outside so I’m sure it will get downgraded.
content.location: From the pull-off headed toward the swim beach walk down and look aross the lake for a small cliff-band/ boulder. There is a tall boulder that would stick out even with a full reservoir behind it about 100yds

content.description: This area is mostly state park with some BLM. The state park is a awesome place to check out regardless if you want to swim, paddle board, fish or climb. There are tons of potential boulders and a handful of potential climbs. Rock quality is definitely mixed, almost everything i have touched is welded tuff with lots of pockets. Unfortunately i have hiked a lot to find out some of the rock is way too fragile to pull on.
